# Splat trailing-slash REMOVED 2026-05-06 — same root cause as above. This
# rule globally 308'd every trailing-slash URL to its no-slash counterpart,
# fighting CF Pages native canonicalisation. Replaced by per-route 200
# rewrites (lines 21+) that match both with and without trailing slash.
# (was: /*/  /:splat  308)

# CODE-AUDIT-023 — case-folding for the legacy PascalCase asset directories.
# The repo carries `Assets/`, `Doc/`, and `Assets/Branding Logo/` in PascalCase
# (with one space-bearing subdir). Linux/CF-Pages is case-sensitive; some
# external links and SEO crawlers normalise to lowercase. Map lowercase
# requests to the PascalCase paths via 200-rewrites so they don't 404.
/assets/*               /Assets/:splat               200
/doc/*                  /Doc/:splat                  200
/assets/branding-logo/* /Assets/Branding%20Logo/:splat 200

# WS-AUDIT-047 (2026-05-10) — Source-CSS exposure.
# Direct requests for /styles.css (the unminified source) are 301-redirected
# to /styles.min.css (the minified, purged production bundle). Prevents
# accidental indexing of the source file by SEO crawlers and reduces edge
# bandwidth by ~150 KB per request. The source CSS is still committed to
# the repo for the build pipeline (scripts/build-css-purged.js consumes it),
# but is NEVER served at the canonical /styles.css URL in production.
/styles.css                  /styles.min.css                              301

# WS-AUDIT-030 (2026-05-10) — 404 status for unmatched URLs.
# Cloudflare Pages SPA-fallback splat: any URL not matched by a file on
# disk OR by the more-specific rules above falls through to here, which
# serves the existing 404.html body with an HTTP 404 status code (instead
# of 200 + arbitrary content, or a generic CF 404 page). MUST remain the
# LAST rule in this file — _redirects matches top-down and a splat earlier
# would shadow the more-specific rules above.
/*                           /404.html                                    404
